===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|benjoin|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|es|en}} {{term|benjuí|lang=es}}, {{etyl|pt|en}} {{term|beijoin|lang=pt}}, {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|benzoi|lang=it}}, from {{etyl|ar|en}} {{term|لبان جاوي|sc=Arab|tr=lubān jāwī|lang=ar||Javanese frankincense}}. The initial ''lu'' was probably lost because it was taken as the definite article in Romance. Compare {{term|oliban}}.

===Pronunciation===
*{{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈbɛnzəʊɪn/|/ˈbɛnzɔɪn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# A resinous substance, dry and brittle, obtained from the {{taxlink|Styrax benzoin|species|noshow=1}}, a tree of Sumatra, Java, etc., having a fragrant odor, and slightly aromatic taste. It is used in the preparation of [[benzoic acid]], in medicine, and as a perfume. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}
# {{context|organic compound|lang=en}} An [[aromatic]] [[hydroxy]] [[ketone]], ''2-hydroxy-1,2-di(phenyl)ethanone'', synthesized from [[benzaldehyde]]; any derivative of this compound. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}
# {{context|botany|lang=en}} The [[spicebush]], ''[[Lindera benzoin]]''. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}

